[size=150][b]Options[/b][/size]
The options menu can be accessed with [b]Middle click[/b] or with [b]Ctrl/Cmd + Left click[/b] on [b]Multi Snippets Inserter[/b] button.
The options window can be accessed by clicking [b]More options[/b] item on the options menu.
[size=120][b]Options menu[/b][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Save to main file:[/b] Save all changes made to the main menu into the items file.
[*] [b]Reload main file:[/b] Reload the items file. This will discard any modification made to the main menu!!!
[*] [b]Edit items file:[/b] Edit the current items file in any text editor.
[*] [b]Backup current items:[/b] Make a backup of the items file.
[*] [b]Open storage folder:[/b] Open the folder where all items files are stored.[/list]
[size=120][b]Options window[/b][/size]
[b][color=red]Note: Read the tooltips of each option in the options window for more detailed information.[/color][/b]
[list]
[*] [b]Convert popup to panel:[/b] Allows you to change the appearance of the main menu into a panel.
[*] [b]Enable context menu:[/b] An item called [b]Create snippet inserter item[/b] will be displayed in the page context menu.
[*] [b]Enable items hotkeys:[/b] Enables the use of hotkeys to insert the snippets from any item.
[*] [b]Evaluator enabled:[/b] Process or ignore all snippets containing [b]Evaluators[/b].
[*] [b]Instant hotkeys:[/b] If enabled, the hotkeys will be created using the "Addon SDK method". If disabled, hotkeys will be created using "key" elements.
[*] [b]Keep selection selected:[/b] If your snippet has a [b]Selection anchor[/b], the current selected text will still be selected after inserting the snippet. This allows you to insert different snippets to the same selection.
[*] [b]Save file expanded:[/b] If enabled, the content of the items file will be saved with a line break at almost every tag (this makes it a little easier to read). If disabled, the content of the items file will be saved in a single line (this makes it hard to read). [b]Note:[/b] This option is useful only for people that doesn't use a proper text editor software. Now a days, any text editor (that deserves to be called as such) has some sort of HTML/XML [i]prettifier[/i].
[*] [b]Show acceltext on items:[/b] If enabled, and item hotkeys are also enabled, the key combination for the hotkey assigned to an item will be displayed next to the item label inside the main menu.
[*] [b]Items file base name:[/b] All items in the main menu are saved into a file. Here can be defined a base name for that file.
[*] [b]Caret anchor placeholder:[/b] Here can be defined the [b]"Caret anchor"[/b]. By default, every time a snippet is inserted, the caret will be positioned at the end of the inserted text. This [b]Caret anchor[/b] placeholder will allow you to position the caret anywhere inside the snippet after its inserted.
[*] [b]Selection anchor placeholder:[/b] Here can be defined the [b]"Selection anchor"[/b]. This placeholder is useful to create snippets to insert HTML/BBCode tags. For example: given the [b]<b>{â–ˆ}</b>[/b] snippet, and some selected text in the current page, the [b]<b>[/b] part of the snippet will be inserted at the [b]beginning[/b] of the selection and the [b]</b>[/b] part of the snippet will be inserted at the [b]end[/b] of the selection.
[*] [b]Evaluator placeholder:[/b] Here can be defined the [b]"Evaluator"[/b]. This placeholder is useful for creating [i]dynamic snippets[/i]. The text surrounded by this placeholders will be evaluated and a string (returned by the evaluated code) will be displayed in its place.
[*] [b]Time stamp for backups:[/b] Here can be chosen the time stamp that will be added to the backup filenames.
[*] [b]Custom time stamp for backups:[/b] Here can be set a custom time stamp format for the items file backups.
[*] [b]Open main menu on hover:[/b] If enabled, the main menu will be automatically opened on mouse over.
[*] [b]Open menu delay:[/b] Delay in seconds to open the main menu on mouse hover.
[*] [b]Close menu delay:[/b] Delay in seconds to close the main menu on mouse out.
[*] [b]Notification position:[/b] Choose in which part of the screen the popup notification generated by this button will appear.[/list]

[color=red][b][size=150]Known issues[/size][/b][/color]
All Gecko applications in which I tried this button handles/renders [i]input elements[/i] and selections in totally different ways. Not to mention the HTML elements with [i]contenteditable[/i] attribute enabled (which by themselves are a total aberration of nature). That made the creation of universal [i]text inserter[/i] and [i]get/set selection[/i] functions an absolute nightmare!!! Considering this, I did my absolute best to make this button work under almost all possible circumstances. This does not rule out the possibility of some [i]quirks[/i]. [color=red]If any error/quirk is found, follow the guidelines found on the [b]Error report[/b] section.[/color]

[color=red][b][size=180]Error report[/size][/b][/color]
[b][color=red]Read the buton help before reporting any error.[/color][/b] Right click on [b]Multi Snippets Inserter[/b] button and click [b]Button help[/b].
